\title{countbcf: Bayesian Causal Forests for Count and Zero-Inflated Count Outcomes}
\description{
\code{countbcf} implements the CountBCF and Zero-Inflated CountBCF
samplers of Souto (2026a, 2026b), which extend the Bayesian Causal Forest
of Hahn, Murray and Carvalho (2020) to count and zero-inflated count
outcomes. The C++ MCMC machinery, the generalized inverse Gaussian (GIG)
leaf prior, and the zero-inflation bookkeeping are reused from the
\code{countbart} source code of Wikle and Zigler (2023)
(\url{https://github.com/nbwikle/estimating-interference}); the
log-linear BART backbone is due to Murray (2021).
}
\section{Main entry point}{

  \itemize{
    \item \code{\link{countbcf}} -- (Zero-Inflated) Bayesian Causal Forest
          for count outcomes. Supports \code{"poisson"}, \code{"nb"},
          \code{"zipoisson"}, and \code{"zinb"} likelihoods.
  }
}

\section{Inherited helpers}{

  The following functions are inherited from the \code{countbart}
  upstream and exposed here for backwards compatibility and to allow
  benchmark comparisons:
  \itemize{
    \item \code{\link{count_bart}} -- log-linear BART count regression
          (no causal decomposition).
    \item \code{\link{bcf_binary}}, \code{\link{bcf_continuous_linear}} --
          BCF samplers for binary and continuous outcomes.
    \item \code{\link{get_forest_fit}}, \code{\link{tree_samples}},
          \code{\link{make_forest}} -- prediction helpers that operate on
          serialized tree traces.
  }
}

